    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel your<strong> potatoes</strong> then chop them into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot of plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-with-creamy-lime-sauce-and-pea-mash/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your<strong> soft cheese </strong>in 75ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[100ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[130ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> soft cheese mixture</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-with-creamy-lime-sauce-and-pea-mash/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes have been cooking for 10 min, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once melted, add your <strong>smoked basa fillet[s]</strong> and cook for 3-4 min on each side or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-with-creamy-lime-sauce-and-pea-mash/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>cooked basa</strong> to a plate and cover with<strong> tin foil</strong> to keep warm</p><p>Reserve the pan</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-with-creamy-lime-sauce-and-pea-mash/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are fork-tender, add your<strong> blanched peas</strong> and cook for 1 min further</p><p>Drain the <strong>potatoes </strong>and<strong> peas </strong>and return them to the pot to steam dry</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-with-creamy-lime-sauce-and-pea-mash/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat with a knob of <strong>butter</strong>, then once melted, add the<strong> sliced garlic</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add the <strong>soft cheese mixture</strong> with a squeeze of <strong>lime juice </strong>and a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Stir it all together and cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce has thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy lime sauce</strong></p><p>Tip: If your sauce is too zingy, add a pinch of salt to temper the acidity</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-with-creamy-lime-sauce-and-pea-mash/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the<strong> drained potatoes </strong>and<strong> peas</strong> to a low heat with a knob of <strong>butter </strong>and a splash of <strong>milk</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and mash together \u2013 this is your <strong>pea mash</strong></p><p>Cut the<strong> remaining lime </strong>into 1 wedge per person</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-with-creamy-lime-sauce-and-pea-mash/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>smoked basa </strong>over the <strong>creamy lime sauce </strong>with the <strong>pea mash </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with a handful of <strong>salad </strong>and a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
